%N A262872 Expansion of (Sum_{i>=0} x^(i^2)) * (Sum_{j>=0} x^(j^3)) / (1-x).
%C A262872 a(n) is number of nonnegative integer solutions (x,y,z) such that x + y^2 + z^3 = n.
%F A262872 G.f.: (Sum_{i>=0} x^(i^2)) * (Sum_{j>=0} x^(j^3)) / (1-x).
%e A262872 a(4) = 5 because there are 5 solutions: (5,0,0), (4,1,0), (4,0,1), (3,1,1) and (1,2,0).
%t A262872 With[{nmax = 75}, CoefficientList[Series[Sum[x^(k^2), {k, 0, nmax}]*Sum[x^(k^3), {k, 0, nmax}]/(1-x), {x, 0, 70}], x]] (* _Georg Fischer_, Jul 03 2026 *)
